<section class="np-local np-section np-reveal" id="local">
  <div class="np-wrap">
    <div class="np-sec-head">
      <p class="np-marker">03 / Local Knowledge</p>
      <h2 class="np-h2">Plumbing in Happy Valley</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="np-rule"></div>

    <div class="np-local-grid">
      <div class="np-local-main">
        <p>
          Happy Valley grew quickly through the 1980s, so a lot of homes here are
          now hitting the age where the original plumbing starts to show its years.
          We see it every week. Galvanised pipes that have corroded from the inside.
          Hot water systems well past their warranty. Drains that were fine for
          thirty years and have finally given up.
        </p>
        <p>
          The established gardens that make this suburb so green are also the reason
          we get so many blocked drain calls. Tree roots find the smallest crack in
          a clay pipe and grow straight into it. A camera inspection shows us exactly
          where the problem is, and pipe relining fixes it without digging up your yard.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="np-pullquote">
          <span class="np-pullquote-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
          We know the streets, the soil, and the homes. That local knowledge means
          we find the real problem faster.
        </blockquote>

        <p>
          Because we work across Happy Valley every day, we know what to look for
          before we arrive. That saves you time, and it saves you money. We give you
          a fixed price up front, so you decide with all the facts in front of you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="np-local-side">
        <p class="np-local-side-head">Common in Happy Valley homes</p>
        <ul class="np-local-side-list">
          <li>Ageing galvanised supply pipes</li>
          <li>Root intrusion in clay drains</li>
          <li>Original hot water systems</li>
          <li>Low pressure from corrosion</li>
          <li>Worn tap and toilet washers</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .np-local-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 62fr 38fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .np-local-main p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.06rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
    color: var(--color-brand-text);
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }
  .np-pullquote {
    margin: 1.75rem 0 1.75rem -2.5rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-style: italic;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 60;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    line-height: 1.18;
    color: var(--color-brand-secondary);
    position: relative;
    max-width: 24ch;
  }
  .np-pullquote-mark {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 4rem;
    line-height: 0;
    color: var(--color-brand-primary);
    position: absolute;
    left: -0.1em;
    top: 0.55em;
  }
  .np-pullquote { padding-left: 1.6em; }

  .np-local-side {
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-brand-primary) 40%, transparent);
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }
  .np-local-side-head {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-brand-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .np-local-side-list { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .np-local-side-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-brand-text);
    padding: 0.65rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-brand-primary) 22%, transparent);
  }
  .np-local-side-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .np-local-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.75rem; }
    .np-pullquote { margin-left: 0; max-width: none; }
  }
</style>
